  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-001","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"The Young Inventor\n\nWhen Sara was twelve years old, she started building small machines in her garage. Her parents didn't understand much about science, but they always encouraged her. She was working on a solar-powered fan when she entered a school science fair. At first, her machine didn't work well, but she didn't give up. She kept testing it every day after school. Finally, on the day of the fair, her fan worked perfectly. She won first place, and a local newspaper wrote a story about her invention. Sara says the most important lesson she learned was that mistakes are part of every discovery.","prompt":"What was Sara building when she entered the science fair?","options":["a robot","a telescope","a solar-powered fan"],"answer":"a solar-powered fan","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-002","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"The Young Inventor\n\nWhen Sara was twelve years old, she started building small machines in her garage. Her parents didn't understand much about science, but they always encouraged her. She was working on a solar-powered fan when she entered a school science fair. At first, her machine didn't work well, but she didn't give up. She kept testing it every day after school. Finally, on the day of the fair, her fan worked perfectly. She won first place, and a local newspaper wrote a story about her invention. Sara says the most important lesson she learned was that mistakes are part of every discovery.","prompt":"Sara's parents understood a lot about science.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-003","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"The Young Inventor\n\nWhen Sara was twelve years old, she started building small machines in her garage. Her parents didn't understand much about science, but they always encouraged her. She was working on a solar-powered fan when she entered a school science fair. At first, her machine didn't work well, but she didn't give up. She kept testing it every day after school. Finally, on the day of the fair, her fan worked perfectly. She won first place, and a local newspaper wrote a story about her invention. Sara says the most important lesson she learned was that mistakes are part of every discovery.","prompt":"What happened at first with her machine?","options":["it exploded","it didn't work well","it worked perfectly"],"answer":"it didn't work well","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-004","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"The Young Inventor\n\nWhen Sara was twelve years old, she started building small machines in her garage. Her parents didn't understand much about science, but they always encouraged her. She was working on a solar-powered fan when she entered a school science fair. At first, her machine didn't work well, but she didn't give up. She kept testing it every day after school. Finally, on the day of the fair, her fan worked perfectly. She won first place, and a local newspaper wrote a story about her invention. Sara says the most important lesson she learned was that mistakes are part of every discovery.","prompt":"Sara gave up after her first failure.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-005","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"The Young Inventor\n\nWhen Sara was twelve years old, she started building small machines in her garage. Her parents didn't understand much about science, but they always encouraged her. She was working on a solar-powered fan when she entered a school science fair. At first, her machine didn't work well, but she didn't give up. She kept testing it every day after school. Finally, on the day of the fair, her fan worked perfectly. She won first place, and a local newspaper wrote a story about her invention. Sara says the most important lesson she learned was that mistakes are part of every discovery.","prompt":"What lesson did Sara learn?","options":["machines are dangerous","mistakes are part of discovery","science is boring"],"answer":"mistakes are part of discovery","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-006","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"A Night in the Library\n\nHamed was preparing for an important science exam. Last Tuesday night, he was studying in the library until very late. While he was reading about famous scientists, he found an old book about Avicenna's work in medicine. He was so interested that he forgot about the time. When the librarian came to close the library, Hamed was still taking notes. He borrowed the book and read it again at home. The next day, he used what he had learned to answer two extra questions on his exam.","prompt":"Where was Hamed studying?","options":["in a laboratory","in the library","at home"],"answer":"in the library","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-007","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"A Night in the Library\n\nHamed was preparing for an important science exam. Last Tuesday night, he was studying in the library until very late. While he was reading about famous scientists, he found an old book about Avicenna's work in medicine. He was so interested that he forgot about the time. When the librarian came to close the library, Hamed was still taking notes. He borrowed the book and read it again at home. The next day, he used what he had learned to answer two extra questions on his exam.","prompt":"Hamed was reading about famous athletes.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-008","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"A Night in the Library\n\nHamed was preparing for an important science exam. Last Tuesday night, he was studying in the library until very late. While he was reading about famous scientists, he found an old book about Avicenna's work in medicine. He was so interested that he forgot about the time. When the librarian came to close the library, Hamed was still taking notes. He borrowed the book and read it again at home. The next day, he used what he had learned to answer two extra questions on his exam.","prompt":"Whose work did Hamed read about?","options":["Edison","Marie Curie","Avicenna"],"answer":"Avicenna","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-009","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"A Night in the Library\n\nHamed was preparing for an important science exam. Last Tuesday night, he was studying in the library until very late. While he was reading about famous scientists, he found an old book about Avicenna's work in medicine. He was so interested that he forgot about the time. When the librarian came to close the library, Hamed was still taking notes. He borrowed the book and read it again at home. The next day, he used what he had learned to answer two extra questions on his exam.","prompt":"Hamed left the library before it closed.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-reading-010","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"A Night in the Library\n\nHamed was preparing for an important science exam. Last Tuesday night, he was studying in the library until very late. While he was reading about famous scientists, he found an old book about Avicenna's work in medicine. He was so interested that he forgot about the time. When the librarian came to close the library, Hamed was still taking notes. He borrowed the book and read it again at home. The next day, he used what he had learned to answer two extra questions on his exam.","prompt":"What did Hamed do with the book?","options":["borrowed it and read it again at home","gave it to his teacher","returned it unread"],"answer":"borrowed it and read it again at home","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-001","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"Which sentence uses past progressive correctly?","options":["She was reading a book.","She reading a book.","She is reading a book yesterday."],"answer":"She was reading a book.","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-002","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"\"The inventor solved the problem himself.\" Himself refers to:","options":["someone else","the inventor","the problem"],"answer":"the inventor","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-003","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"Choose the correct word: A person who studies to find new facts is a ________.","options":["hunter","researcher","traveler"],"answer":"researcher","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-004","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"\"She never gave up.\" Gave up means:","options":["continued","quit","succeeded"],"answer":"quit","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-005","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"Which sentence is a question in past progressive?","options":["Were they studying?","Did they studying?","Are they studying?"],"answer":"Were they studying?","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-006","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"\"Belief\" means:","options":["something you doubt","something you believe is true","something you forget"],"answer":"something you believe is true","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-007","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"Choose the correct reflexive pronoun: \"I did it ______.\"","options":["himself","myself","themselves"],"answer":"myself","difficulty":"easy"},
  {"id":"g10-l3-mixed-008","grade":10,"lesson":3,"lessonTitle":"The Value of Knowledge","section":"mixed","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","prompt":"Which verb is a state verb?","options":["running","know","writing"],"answer":"know","difficulty":"easy"},
